name: Avocado Toast
instructions: Toast the bread.
Mash the avocado with lemon juice, salt, and pepper.
Spread avocado mixture on toasted bread.

name: Greek Yogurt Parfait
instructions: Layer yogurt, honey, granola, and berries in a glass.
Repeat layers and serve.

name: Quinoa Salad
instructions: Cook quinoa according to package instructions.
Chop cucumber and cherry tomatoes.
Mix quinoa, cucumber, tomatoes, and feta.
Whisk olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper, and toss with the salad.

name: Chicken Wraps
instructions: Cook chicken breast and slice it.
Spread mayonnaise and mustard on tortillas.
Add lettuce, tomato, and chicken.
Wrap and serve.

name: Beef Stir-Fry
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Add garlic and ginger, then beef strips, and cook until browned.
Add bell peppers and onion, stir-fry until tender.
Add soy sauce and mix well.

name: Vegetarian Chili
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pot.
Sauté onion and bell pepper until soft.
Add beans, corn, tomato sauce, and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes and serve.

name: Hummus and Veggies
instructions: Serve hummus with carrot, cucumber, and bell pepper sticks.

name: Cheese and Crackers
instructions: Arrange cheese slices on crackers and serve.

name: Apple Pie
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Peel and slice apples, then toss with sugar and cinnamon.
Place apple mixture into pie crust, dot with butter, and cover with another crust.
Bake for 45 minutes.

name: Brownies
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Melt butter and mix with sugar and cocoa powder.
Add eggs and vanilla extract, then flour.
Pour into a baking dish and bake for 25 minutes.

name: Smoothie Bowl
instructions: Blend banana, berries, and Greek yogurt until smooth.
Pour into bowls and top with honey and granola.

name: Egg Muffins
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Whisk eggs with milk, then mix in spinach and cheese.
Pour mixture into muffin tin and bake for 20 minutes.

name: Turkey Sandwich
instructions: Spread mayonnaise on bread slices.
Layer turkey, lettuce, and tomato between two slices of bread.

name: Tomato Soup
instructions: Sauté onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add chopped tomatoes and vegetable broth.
Simmer for 30 minutes and blend until smooth.

name: Salmon with Asparagus
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Place salmon fillets and asparagus on a baking sheet.
Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice.
Bake for 20 minutes.

name: Pasta Primavera
instructions: Cook pasta according to package instructions.
Sauté chopped vegetables in olive oil until tender.
Toss pasta with vegetables and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

name: Trail Mix
instructions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve.

name: Yogurt with Honey
instructions: Drizzle honey over Greek yogurt and serve.

name: Cheesecake
instructions: Preheat oven to 160°C (320°F).
Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter and press into a springform pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar, then add eggs and vanilla extract.
Pour filling into crust and bake for 50 minutes.

name: Berry Crumble
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix berries with sugar and place in a baking dish.
Combine flour, butter, and oats to make crumble topping.
Sprinkle topping over berries and bake for 30 minutes.

name: Breakfast Burritos
instructions: Scramble eggs and mix with cheese and ham.
Place mixture in tortillas and roll up.
Serve with salsa.

name: Smoothie
instructions: Blend all ingredients until smooth and serve.

name: Chicken Caesar Wrap
instructions: Combine chicken, Caesar dressing, lettuce, and parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Wrap mixture in tortillas and serve.

name: Stuffed Bell Peppers
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Cook ground beef and rice, mix with tomato sauce and onion.
Stuff mixture into bell peppers and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

name: Chicken Alfredo
instructions: Cook fettuccine according to package instructions.
Cook chicken and slice it.
Heat cream and butter in a pan, then add cheese to make Alfredo sauce.
Toss pasta with sauce and chicken.

name: Vegetable Stir-Fry
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Add garlic and ginger, then mixed vegetables.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender, add soy sauce, and serve.

name: Peanut Butter Banana Bites
instructions: Slice banana and spread peanut butter on slices.
Top with chocolate chips and serve.

name: Apple Slices with Almond Butter
instructions: Slice apple and serve with almond butter for dipping.

name: Panna Cotta
instructions: Heat cream and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add gelatin and vanilla extract, stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into molds and chill until set.

name: Lemon Bars
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix flour, sugar, and butter to make crust, then press into a baking dish.
Mix eggs, sugar, and lemon juice for filling and pour over crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.

name: Chia Pudding
instructions: Mix chia seeds, milk, and honey.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with fruit before serving.

name: Oatmeal
instructions: Cook oats in milk until soft.
Stir in honey and top with fruit.

name: Tuna Salad
instructions: Mix tuna with mayonnaise, celery, and onion.
Serve with crackers or on a sandwich.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: Slice tomatoes and mozzarella cheese.
Layer with basil leaves, drizzle with balsamic vinegar, and serve.

name: Beef Tacos
instructions: Cook ground beef with taco seasoning.
Fill taco shells with beef, lettuce, cheese, and salsa.

name: Pork Chops with Apples
instructions: Cook pork chops in olive oil until browned.
Add sliced apples and onion, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook until apples are tender.

name: Stuffed Dates
instructions: Stuff dates with cream cheese and top with nuts.

name: Fruit Salad
instructions: Mix fruit with honey and lime juice, and serve.

name: Chocolate Mousse
instructions: Melt chocolate and let cool.
Whip cream with sugar, fold in chocolate, and refrigerate until set.

name: Apple Crisp
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix apples with a bit of sugar and place in a baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, oats, flour, and butter for topping, sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 40 minutes.

name: Fruit Smoothie
instructions: Blend all ingredients until smooth and serve.

name: Bagel with Lox
instructions: Spread cream cheese on bagels.
Top with smoked salmon and capers.

name: Veggie Wrap
instructions: Spread hummus on tortillas.
Add sliced cucumber, bell peppers, and spinach.
Wrap and serve.

name: Chicken Noodle Soup
instructions: Cook chicken in broth, then shred.
Add noodles, carrots, and celery, and simmer until noodles are cooked.

name: Stuffed Chicken Breast
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix spinach and cream cheese, stuff into chicken breasts.
Season with garlic, and cook in olive oil until done.

name: Shrimp Scampi
instructions: Cook shrimp in butter and garlic until pink.
Add lemon juice and parsley, serve over pasta.

name: Veggie Chips
instructions: Slice vegetables thinly and toss with olive oil and salt.
Bake at 180°C (350°F) until crispy.

name: Cheese and Crackers
instructions: Serve cheese with crackers.

name: Brownies
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs and cocoa powder.
Fold in flour and bake for 25 minutes.

name: Banana Bread
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mash bananas and mix with sugar, flour, eggs, and melted butter.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake for 60 minutes.

name: Avocado Toast
instructions: Toast bread and spread mashed avocado mixed with lemon juice, salt, and pepper.

name: Egg Muffins
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix eggs, spinach, cheese, and milk.
Pour into muffin tin and bake for 20 minutes.

name: Quinoa Salad
instructions: Cook quinoa according to package instructions.
Mix with chopped vegetables, feta cheese, olive oil, and lemon juice.

name: Greek Salad
instructions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve.

name: Chicken Parmesan
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Bread chicken breasts with breadcrumbs and bake until cooked.
Top with marinara sauce and mozzarella cheese, bake until cheese is melted.

name: Lemon Herb Chicken
instructions: Marinate chicken breasts in lemon juice, herbs, and olive oil.
Cook in a pan or bake until done.

name: Beef Stir-Fry
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Add beef strips and cook until browned.
Add vegetables and soy sauce, stir-fry until vegetables are tender.

name: Rice Cakes with Nut Butter
instructions: Spread nut butter on rice cakes and serve.

name: Cucumber Sandwiches
instructions: Spread cream cheese on bread, add sliced cucumber, and assemble sandwiches.

name: Pineapple Upside-Down Cake
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Melt butter and brown sugar in a pan, then pour into a baking dish.
Place pineapple slices on top, mix flour, eggs, and baking powder, and pour over pineapple.
Bake for 35 minutes.

name: Peach Cobbler
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).
Mix peaches with sugar and place in a baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, butter, and baking powder for topping, sprinkle over peaches.
Bake for 40 minutes.
